@startuml
' @id(DOM-DEPLOY-IAC)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
'
' Objective-side domain model of the IaC artifact /mdd-deploy generates.
' Refines the current single-dialect (Bicep-only) model: the operator
' now picks ONE dialect per run via a DialectChoice that MUST be
' confirmed before any artifact is written (no silent default). Both
' concrete artifacts share the SAME secured Azure topology and satisfy
' the SAME invariants — full parity; only structure differs.
'
' Stereotypes here are documentation-only per the deploy profile; this
' file carries NO security-parity markers (/mdd-deploy is outside the
' parity gate). Package label is slash-free (PlantUML treats / and ..
' in package names as namespace separators and crashes).
'
' @desc(DOM-DEPLOY-IAC, "Objective: /mdd-deploy supports two IaC dialects, one per run. A DialectChoice (value in {bicep, terraform}, confirmed:Boolean) gates artifact creation — nothing is written until confirmed (OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-DIALECT, OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-CONFIRM-BEFORE-ARTIFACT). BicepIaC (main.bicep + modules -> ARM JSON) and TerraformIaC (main.tf + modules, azurerm provider, remote state backend, -> az/terraform apply) both compose the identical secured topology — ACR, Container Apps env + revision (ingress 8080, non-root), Azure DB for PostgreSQL (TLS), Key Vault (Deny + bypass=AzureServices when peers private), Azure OpenAI, pre-traffic migration job — and satisfy the same secure-by-default + migration-order invariants. The skill writes files and STOPS; it never deploys.")
title /mdd-deploy generated IaC structure (objective — two dialects)

class DialectChoice <<gate>> {
  value : {bicep | terraform}
  confirmed : Boolean
  rule = exactly one dialect per run
  rule = no artifact written until confirmed
  rule = no silent default
}

abstract class IaCArtifact <<artifact>> {
  target = azure-container-apps (v1, only)
  generatedBy = /mdd-deploy (writes files, never deploys)
  appliedBy = operator
}
class BicepIaC <<artifact>> {
  language = Bicep (Azure-native ARM DSL)
  entrypoint = main.bicep
  structure = main.bicep + Bicep modules
  transpilesTo = ARM (Azure Resource Manager) JSON
  appliedVia = az deployment
}
class TerraformIaC <<artifact>> {
  language = Terraform HCL
  entrypoint = main.tf
  structure = main.tf + modules
  provider = azurerm
  stateBackend = remote (azurerm backend)
  appliedVia = terraform plan + apply
}

class ContainerRegistry <<Azure ACR>>
class ContainerAppsEnv <<Azure Container Apps>>
class AppRevision <<Azure Container Apps>> {
  ingress = 8080 external
  user = non-root
  env = NODE_ENV=production
}
class PostgresFlexibleServer <<Azure DB for PostgreSQL>> {
  transport = sslmode=require
  encryption = at-rest
}
class KeyVault <<Azure Key Vault>> {
  holds = every secret (Container Apps secret refs)
  networkDefaultAction = Deny
  bypass = AzureServices
}
class AzureOpenAI <<Azure OpenAI>>
class MigrationJob <<Azure Container Apps Job>> {
  order = before any revision traffic routing
}

DialectChoice "1" --> "1" IaCArtifact : selects & gates
IaCArtifact <|-- BicepIaC
IaCArtifact <|-- TerraformIaC

IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" ContainerRegistry
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" ContainerAppsEnv
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" KeyVault
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" PostgresFlexibleServer
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" AzureOpenAI
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" MigrationJob
ContainerAppsEnv "1" *-- "1..*" AppRevision
AppRevision ..> ContainerRegistry : pull image
AppRevision ..> KeyVault : secret references
AppRevision ..> PostgresFlexibleServer : <<Encrypt>> TLS (sslmode=require)
AppRevision ..> AzureOpenAI : API key (landmine: NOT managed identity)
MigrationJob ..> PostgresFlexibleServer : <<Encrypt>> schema migrate
MigrationJob "1" --> "1" AppRevision : completes BEFORE\ntraffic routing

note bottom of DialectChoice
  Mandatory blocking confirmation BEFORE any deploy
  artifact (diagram.puml, generated IaC, runbook.md).
  Invariants: OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-DIALECT (value in the set,
  exactly one) and OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-CONFIRM-BEFORE-ARTIFACT
  (artifact => confirmed; no silent default).
end note

note bottom of KeyVault
  Secure-by-default, identical for BOTH dialects:
  when Postgres + Azure OpenAI are private, Key Vault
  is generated with networkAcls.defaultAction='Deny'
  + bypass='AzureServices' (or a private endpoint).
  Invariant: OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SECURE-BY-DEFAULT.
end note

note bottom of IaCArtifact
  FULL PARITY: BicepIaC and TerraformIaC compose the
  same secured topology and satisfy the same invariant
  checklist; only language/structure/state differ.
  Produced by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE; written into
  CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SECURE-BY-DEFAULT / -MIGRATION-ORDER.
end note
@enduml
